  <h1>Advanced Class Syllabus</h1>
  <p>This curriculum is practical-first. Each module ends with a lab checklist and a small project.</p>
  <article class="mod">
    <h3>Module 1 — Android System & Environment</h3>
    <ul><li>AOSP overview; services & build blocks</li><li>ADB, fastboot & device lab setup</li><li><em>Lab:</em> Provision emulator + device; capture logs</li></ul>
  </article>
  <article class="mod">
    <h3>Module 2 — App Components & IPC</h3>
    <ul><li>Activities, Services, Broadcasts, Content Providers</li><li>Permissions, intents, deep links</li><li><em>Lab:</em> Inspect components; craft intents</li></ul>
  </article>
  <article class="mod">
    <h3>Module 3 — Security Model & Hardening</h3>
    <ul><li>Sandboxing, SELinux, storage & network security</li><li>Secrets & config best practices</li><li><em>Lab:</em> Threat-model a sample app</li></ul>
  </article>
  <article class="mod">
    <h3>Module 4 — Reverse Engineering Basics</h3>
    <ul><li>Decompilation, manifest analysis, signatures</li><li>Intro to instrumentation & tracing</li><li><em>Lab:</em> Extract signals safely</li></ul>
  </article>
  <article class="mod">
    <h3>Module 5 — Projects & Reviews</h3>
    <ul><li>Build analysis scripts or mini tools</li><li>Peer review & feedback</li><li><em>Lab:</em> Harden a sample app</li></ul>
  </article>
